                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/mech-321" class="program-course-title">
              MECH 321 Mechanics of Deformable Solids (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29822" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mechanical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mechanical Engineering              : Modern phenomenological theories of the behaviour of engineering materials. Stress and strain concepts and introduction to constitutive theory. Applications of theory of elasticity and thermoelasticity. Introduction to finite element stress analysis methods.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

