                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/mech-331" class="program-course-title">
              MECH 331 Fluid Mechanics 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29824" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mechanical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mechanical Engineering              : Physical properties of fluids. Kinematics and dynamics of fluid flow: stress in a continuum, rates of strain, rotation. Control volume analysis; conservation of mass, linear momentum and energy; Euler and Bernoulli equations; Flow measurement. Dimensional analysis and dynamical similarity. Laminar and turbulent flow in pipes and boundary layers.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Timothy Lee (Fall)                  Luca Cortelezzi (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-1-5)</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: MECH 210. Pre/Co-requisites: MECH 220, MECH 240, MATH 271.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
