                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/mech-346" class="program-course-title">
              MECH 346 Heat Transfer (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29828" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mechanical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mechanical Engineering              : Basic concepts and overview. Steady and unsteady heat conduction. Fin Theory. Convective heat transfer: governing equations; dimensionless parameters; analogy between momentum and heat transfer. Design correlations for forced, natural, and mixed convection. Heat exchangers. Radiative heat transfer: black- and gray-body radiation; shape factors; enclosure theory. Thermal engineering design project.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Bantwal Baliga (Fall)                  Laurent B Mydlarski (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-1-5)</li>
              <li>Prerequisites: MECH 240 or BREE 301, MECH 331 or BREE 305, MATH 271 or BREE 319</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
